<a href="https://www.macrumors.com/guide/apple-music/">Apple Music</a> and <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/roundup/apple-tv/">Apple TV</a> are experiencing an outage that could be causing issues for some users, according to <a href="https://www.apple.com/support/systemstatus/">Apple's System Status page</a>.<br/>
<br/>
<img src="https://images.macrumors.com/article-new/2025/10/Apple-TV-Color.jpg" alt="" width="1600" height="900" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1023382" /><br/>
The outage started at 2:53 p.m. Eastern Time, and it is impacting &zwnj;Apple Music&zwnj;, &zwnj;Apple TV&zwnj;, and &zwnj;Apple TV&zwnj; Channels. Apple says that some users may run into intermittent problems, though specifics have not been provided. There don't appear to be a large number of complaints about the services on social media at this time.<br/>
<br/>
We'll update this article when Apple's services are back up and running.<br/>
<br/>
<b>Update:</b> Game Center has also been added to the list of services affected by an outage. <br/>
<br/>
<b>Update 2:</b> As of 4:57 p.m Eastern Time, Apple says the outages have been fixed. <br/>This article, &quot;<a href="https://www.macrumors.com/2025/12/10/apple-tv-apple-music-outage/">Apple Music and Apple TV Experiencing Outage [Update: Fixed]</a>&quot; first appeared on <a href="https://www.macrumors.com">MacRumors.com</a><br/><br/><a href="https://forums.macrumors.com/threads/apple-music-and-apple-tv-experiencing-outage-update-fixed.2474491/">Discuss this article</a> in our forums<br/><br/>